cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DB. 

The paper presents a Web API for accessing and consuming graph embeddings, which are commonly used in natural language processing and information retrieval tasks. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are likely sub-categories. The paper also evaluates the semantic value of the trained models, which suggests a focus on machine learning and specifically, deep learning. This makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper deals with knowledge graphs, which are a type of database, so cs.DB (Databases) is also a possible sub-category.
